reviews.review: I thought this star wars was really surprising, mysterious, and probably one of the best shot of the star wars franchise. It really focuses on the force, sith, and jedi. If you're a handcore star wars nerd/fan you'll really enjoy this. If not then you'll walk out confused and like meh lol
Avoid this movie like the plague.

Why I despise Disney and all it's (modern) works... in one easy lesson.
 I believe Walt would be deeply upset. In fact, the only Star Wars thing I've liked recently was Rogue One. And I'm a diehard fan - of the original three, more so the first two.
I'll stick to the theatrical releases of the original three. Glad we can sweep the rest under the carpet now and forget they existed. Awesome CGI absolutely wasted, and vanilla popsicle girl is so wholly lacklustre - y'all know who I'm talking about.
What happened to actors with depth and personality? I saw Joker eight times... I didn't even want to finish this.
BEST OF THE THREE!!! nothing is going to beat the original trilogy but the critics are wrong amazing movie from the plot to acting!
Truly wonderful book and to an uneven trilogy. I really liked episode 7....8 was a little uneven for me ...Rise of Skywalker really just hit it home and brought a lot of good closure.

The Last Jedi kind of made it impossible for this one to be truly great. The ending was deeply, deeply dissatisfying. The rest was one big fetch quest. An abundance of fanservice moments can't save this from being a sour end to the story of Skywalker.

The movie had it's moments which were fine, the action was generally fun, the lightsaber stuff was fine, the cinematography was well done. However the pase was much to high, it felt is if 2 movies were forced into one movie, there was little to no character development, the third act was way over the top, and finally our nostalgia for the movies was weaponized far to heavily. However I walked out of the cinema feeling that i was entertained. People saying that it is worse than the phantom menace and attack of the clones arr a bit exaggerating in my opinion.
Should have given the third part to Rian Johnson as well...

Film is rushed and often feels like there is no structure. Poor dialogue is paired with one dimensional characters for an unsatisfying and undeserved resolution. Gorgeous cinematography and visual FXs could not save the dire plot
